my apple i pod freezes what can i do to make it play this is easy my ipod froze like times already to make your ipod work again you have reset your ipod to it's original state all you have to do is using your usb cable plug the i pod to the computer then toggle the hold switch on and off a few times and then restart it by holding the menu and select middle at the same time until the screen goes black and the apple logo is up good luck IPod Apple Computer IPod nano IPod shuffle IPod mini IPod photo IMac FireWire ITunes Embedded system Mouse (computing) USB flash drive Apple Macintosh Digital audio player Universal Serial Bus FairPlay PlayStation Portable Apple typography Apple II family ITunes Music Store Mac mini Creative Zen Booting Gradius Pump It Up Podcasting Apple Desktop Bus Sonic the Hedgehog (16-bit) Atari 8-bit family Disc jockey Dance Dance Revolution EXTREME Floppy disk Plug-and-play Game Boy Advance Touchpad Mac OS X v10.4 Dance Dance Revolution ULTRAMIX High fidelity Musical Instrument Digital Interface Dance Dance Revolution ULTRAMIX 2 Jack plug D-subminiature DDRMAX: Dance Dance Revolution Laptop DDRMAX2: Dance Dance Revolution Commodore 64 DDRMAX2: Dance Dance Revolution 7thMIX Mach kernel Dance Dance Revolution EXTREME (North America) Danger Hiptop Secure Digital card IBM PC keyboard Chicago (typeface) DDRMAX: Dance Dance Revolution 6thMIX Digital rights management Apple Newton Game Boy Computer bus Oscilloscope SCART History of the graphical user interface Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic Walkman History of Microsoft Windows Desktop computer Flip-flop (electronics) AlphaSmart H.264/MPEG-4 AVC Sega Mega Drive/Sega Genesis Flash memory Common Unix Printing System Archos The End of the World (Doctor Who) Television USB mass storage device class Switch RS-232 Apple IIGS Napster (pay service) ILife Screenshot Macintosh Finder Handheld video game Windows XP Diablo II: Lord of Destruction Atari 2600 Modchip WordPerfect Final Fantasy Apple Store IBoo